<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10831] Fix the way we replace sstables after anticompaction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10831</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have a bug when we replace sstables after anticompaction, we keep adding duplicates which causes leveled compaction to fail after. Reason being that LCS does not keep its sstables in a &lt;tt&gt;Set&lt;/tt&gt;, so after first compaction, we will keep around removed sstables in the leveled manifest and that will put LCS in an infinite loop as it tries to mark non-existing sstables as compacting&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12920407">CASSANDRA-10831</key>
            <summary>Fix the way we replace sstables after anticompaction</summary>
